                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item-content" style="font-size: 16px ;text-transform: none ;color: #8f8f8f ;">
                                                        <p>CII - Indian Green Building Council - IGBC launched 18th IGBC Student chapter - Arc Institute of Technical Education (ARCITE), Kollam, Kerala. The event was launched through virtual medium by Ar B.R. Ajit, Chairman, IGBC Cochin Chapter.</p>
                                                        <p>Ar B.R.Ajit delivered a special address to the students and faculties and Ar Sri Rekha, Counsellor, IGBC gave a detailed presentation on IGBC Green Education. The institution has also taken an innovative Green initiative – <strong>‘PLANT THE FUTURE’</strong> As part of this, for every new admission, the student will be provided a tree sapling which will be planted in his/her name. </p>
														<p>Ar B.R.Ajit, Chairman, IGBC Cochin Chapter provided insight on IGBC and its leadership role in building a Greener India. Highlighted IGBC’s vision and its associations with leading institutions across the country. Ar Sri Rekha, Counsellor, IGBC discussed about IGBC Green Education course; Career opportunity and growth prospects in the field of Green Buildings and Sustainability.</p>
